WEBVTT

00:00:00.020 --> 00:00:02.310
Before I start, I want to thank the AdScience

00:00:02.310 --> 00:00:06.270
team for the invitation, and especially a special thank you out

00:00:06.310 --> 00:00:08.630
to Matthew and Ronan for helping me get this presentation sorted

00:00:08.670 --> 00:00:08.820
.

00:00:08.840 --> 00:00:11.140
And of course, thank you to the BlueSky and

00:00:11.190 --> 00:00:14.330
AdProto teams for making this kind of more possible.

00:00:14.360 --> 00:00:18.830
SkySquare is a Chrome and Brave extension built on

00:00:18.830 --> 00:00:20.000
AdProto.

00:00:20.020 --> 00:00:23.350
Yeah, we can also just send it out because nothing else

00:00:23.350 --> 00:00:24.180
works.

00:00:24.200 --> 00:00:28.260
The conversation about external sources on the web, SkySqu

00:00:28.260 --> 00:00:33.000
are aggregates and presents that commentary directly on the page inside

00:00:33.130 --> 00:00:35.960
a sidebar on the browser, so you can see the

00:00:35.960 --> 00:00:38.430
commentary in context while you read.

00:00:38.460 --> 00:00:42.450
To demonstrate how the application works, we've imagined a fictional

00:00:42.510 --> 00:00:46.140
research setting, ResearchOne University, and its Animal Cogn

00:00:46.220 --> 00:00:47.070
ition Lab.

00:00:47.100 --> 00:00:49.020
You'll be hearing from...

00:00:54.200 --> 00:01:01.820
PI at ResearchOne University's Animal Cognition Lab.

00:01:01.840 --> 00:01:04.660
I use SkySquare to see how people are in

00:01:04.660 --> 00:01:06.610
terms of people and ideas.

00:01:06.880 --> 00:01:12.310
Or if we figure it out later, we can always try

00:01:12.360 --> 00:01:14.880
to come back to it.

00:01:14.900 --> 00:01:17.270
Okay, so yeah, thank you.

00:01:17.300 --> 00:01:18.720
This is the first half of the day.

00:01:19.860 --> 00:01:22.040
We have unconference boards in the back, so if you

00:01:22.040 --> 00:01:24.610
had questions or things you want to make sure you're remembering

00:01:24.960 --> 00:01:27.170
, we're encouraging you to add a post-it note

00:01:27.170 --> 00:01:28.660
on the unconference board.

00:01:28.680 --> 00:01:31.550
And other than that, yeah, we'll just be back

00:01:31.590 --> 00:01:32.480
here at 1.

00:01:32.700 --> 00:01:33.260
30.

00:01:33.280 --> 00:01:34.280
Thanks, everyone, so far.

00:01:34.300 --> 00:01:35.000
It's been awesome.

00:01:35.020 --> 00:01:35.960
See you soon.
